				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, we were right. Each group can do their own HO's. We made one group our "HO group" and let the other group take over heals and magic damage. It worked pretty effectively, we were able to get some nice damage done.
<br />

<br />
Lyrima, some of the HO's require one of each class to contribute. You just have to pick starter chains that your group can do. If you are without a mage, you can work on the "Verdant Trinity" line of HO's. Although, they are mostly buffs. 
<br />

<br />
And I believe that there was a typo, scouts don't have a blue horn. Mendoza probably just put it in there to make sure you were paying attention  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
